name: Galileo L14 (FOC FM33 & FM34)
location_str: Ariane Launch Area 4 @ Guiana Space Centre, GUF
description: Payload consists of two satellites for Europe's Galileo navigation system.
program_description: Galileo is a global navigation satellite system (GNSS) that went live in 2016, created by the European Union through the European Space Agency (ESA), operated by the European Union Agency for the Space Programme (EUSPA).
rocket_fact: Astronauts on the International Space Station witness 16 sunrises and sunsets every single day.
